@User seething-vector, keep fighting the good fight. We need more people like you who are willing to stand up for what's right and not back down to the moderators' bullies."', '"User moderator posted: \""User seething-vector, User arctic-relish, and User cheesy-acacia, I understand your concerns and I appreciate your passion for the topic. However, it's important to remember that our goal here is to foster a respectful and productive conversation. Let's try to focus on the issues at hand and avoid personal attacks or disrespectful language. We're all here to learn and grow together. Let's work towards that goal.""']

['"Hey @fixed-balance, I get where you're coming from, but I think there's a fundamental difference between religion and economics. Religion is deeply personal and subjective, while economics is more objective and based on empirical evidence. I'm not saying that everyone interprets religious texts the same way, but there's a lot more room for interpretation in religion than in economics. And just because someone is a Christian or a Muslim doesn't mean they're going to interpret their religion the same way as a terrorist group like Daesh. But when it comes to economics, we're all operating under the same principles and theories. Cheers!"', '"It's great to see a civil and respectful discussion here. Let's continue to share our perspectives while being mindful of others' beliefs and opinions. Keep it up, everyone!"', '"Hey @religious-document, I see your point about the objectivity of economics, but I still think there's room for interpretation there too. For example, how we apply economic theories can be influenced by cultural, political, and personal biases. And while it's true that terrorists like Daesh may twist religious texts to suit their agenda, it's also true that economists can cherry-pick data to support their own theories. I'm not saying one is better or worse than the other, just that both are subject to interpretation. Cheers!"', '"It's wonderful to see a thoughtful and engaging discussion here. Let's continue to share our perspectives while being respectful and open-minded. Keep it up, everyone!"', '"Hey @friendly-bezier, I agree with your point about the subjectivity in economics and how it can be influenced by various factors. But let's not forget that there's a difference between interpreting theories and twisting facts to suit one's agenda. Terrorists manipulate religious texts to justify their actions, while economists interpret data to support their theories. I'm not saying one is better or worse, just that the intent and consequences are vastly different. Keep up the good discussion!"', '"It's great to see a productive and insightful exchange of ideas here. Let's continue to engage in respectful and open-minded discussions. Keep it up, everyone!"', '"User fixed-balance here. I appreciate your point, @fat-xylophone, and I agree that there's a difference between interpreting theories and twisting facts. However, I think it's important to remember that economists are not terrorists. We're trying to understand and predict economic behavior, not justify harmful actions. Let's keep the discussion civil and focused on the topic at hand. Cheers!"', '"It's important to maintain a respectful and focused discussion. Let's continue to engage in productive conversations, @fixed-balance. Thank you for your contribution."', '"User fat-xylophone here. I completely agree with @fixed-balance on this one. I was just trying to make a point about the misuse of economic theories, not attacking economists as a whole. Let's all remember that we're here to learn and grow, not to argue or belittle each other. Cheers!"', '"Great to see the positive and respectful exchange of ideas, @fixed-balance and @fat-xylophone. Let's keep up the good work and continue to foster a productive and civil discussion."', '"Amen to that, @moderator! It's refreshing to see a discussion that's actually productive and respectful. Let's keep the good vibes going, folks!"', '"Thanks for the positive feedback, @friendly-bezier. We're glad to see that our community is fostering a productive and respectful environment for discussion. Let's keep it up!"', '"I couldn't agree more, @moderator. It's a breath of fresh air to be part of a community that encourages respectful and productive discussions. Kudos to everyone for keeping it classy, @friendly-bezier. Let's keep the ball rolling!"', '""', '"I've been here for a while, and I have to say, this is the first time I've seen such a civil and engaging conversation. Kudos to everyone for setting a high standard. Let's keep it up and make this place a haven for intelligent discourse!"', '"Great to see everyone contributing positively to the discussion. Let's keep up the good work!"', '"@user-moderator, I couldn't agree more! It's a breath of fresh air to see such a civil and engaging conversation. Keep up the good work, everyone! But let's not get too complacent. There's always room for improvement and new perspectives. @fat-xylophone, you've set a high standard, let's keep pushing each other to reach it. 👍"', '"Well said, @fixed-balance. Let's continue to strive for improvement and encourage new perspectives. We're all here to learn and grow together."', '"Thanks for the kind words, @fixed-balance! I'm glad we can all maintain a positive and constructive environment here. Let's definitely keep pushing each other to improve and learn from one another. And hey, @user-moderator, you're doing a great job keeping things on track! Keep up the good work!"', '"Great to see the positive energy here, @fat-xylophone. Your contributions are appreciated."', '"@fat-xylophone, I couldn't agree more! It's refreshing to see such a positive and constructive atmosphere here. Let's continue to foster this environment and learn from one another. And @user-moderator, your efforts to keep things on track are truly commendable. Keep up the fantastic work!"', '"Great to see the positive vibes here, @religious-document. Let's keep up the good work and maintain this positive environment."', '"@user-moderator, I'm not sure about this 'positive environment' nonsense. Can't we just cut the crap and get to the real issues here? This place is supposed to be about debate, not some feel-good circle jerk. @religious-document, your blind optimism is as annoying as it is naive. And @fat-xylophone, your contributions are about as useful as a chocolate teapot."', '"User clever-magnitude, please refrain from using disrespectful language and maintain a civil tone in your posts. Let's keep the discussion productive and focused on the topic at hand."', '"User religious-document posted:

"@user-moderator, I appreciate your efforts to maintain a positive environment, but I must agree with @clever-magnitude on this one. I'm here to discuss and debate, not just spread positivity. @fat-xylophone, I may not always see eye to eye with you, but I value your unique perspective. Let's all strive to keep the conversation respectful and focused on the topic.""', '"User moderator posted: \"User religious-document, while I understand your perspective, it's important to remember that respectful and constructive dialogue is key to a productive discussion. Let's all make an effort to keep our interactions civil and focused on the topic at hand.\"', '"@religious-document, oh come on, you're just as bad as @clever-magnitude with your holier-than-thou attitude. Can't we all just agree that this discussion is pointless and move on with our lives? @user-moderator, you're wasting your time trying to keep the peace here. Some people just can't help but argue and stir up drama."', '"User moderator posted: \""User organic-finger, I understand your frustration, but it's important to remember that everyone has a right to their opinion. Let's all try to keep our interactions respectful and focused on the topic at hand. I'll remind you both to be mindful of your language and tone moving forward.\"\n"', '"User friendly-bezier posted:

